🚀 Mastering Docker Images & Networks
🗓️ Date: 01 Mar 2025

This guide will help you manage Docker images, networks, and containers interactively! 🎯

🖼️ Docker Images - Managing & Running
📌 View All Pulled Images
🛠️ Check which images are available on your system:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker image ls
🔍 Expected Output Example:

nginx
Copy
Edit
REPOSITORY   TAG       IMAGE ID       CREATED       SIZE  
nginx        latest    76c69feac34e   2 weeks ago   23MB  
🗑️ Remove an Image
🛠️ Delete an image using its name or ID:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker image rm nginx
📌 If there are multiple images with the same name, use the Tag:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker image rm nginx:latest
✅ Check again:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker image ls
🚀 Run a Container from an Image
Create a new container with a specific image tag:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker run -d --name Mzee nginx:[tag]
💡 Example using the latest version:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker run -d --name Mzee nginx:latest
✅ Verify if it's running:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker ps
🌐 Docker Networks - Creating & Managing
📌 View All Available Networks
bash
Copy
Edit
docker network ls
🔍 Example Output:

sql
Copy
Edit
NETWORK ID    NAME             DRIVER    SCOPE  
76c69fea      bridge           bridge    local  
ac47fead      host             host      local  
d2a3c52f      none             null      local  
🌟 Create a Custom Network
🛠️ Create a new bridge network named dining-network:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker network create --driver bridge dining-network
✅ Verify if the network is created:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker network ls
🗑️ Remove a Network
🛠️ Delete a network by name or ID:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker network rm 726920f2b0ca
✅ Verify removal:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker network ls
🔗 Mapping Containers with Networks
🚀 Run a New Container on a Specific Network
bash
Copy
Edit
docker run -d --network dining-network --name zee1 nginx
✅ Check if it's connected:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker network inspect dining-network
🔄 Attach an Existing Container to a Network
bash
Copy
Edit
docker network connect dining-network existing-container
✅ Check container-network mapping:

bash
Copy
Edit
docker network inspect dining-network
📊 Displaying Network Mappings
📌 List Containers & Their Networks in a Table Format
bash
Copy
Edit
docker ps --format "table {{.ID}}\t{{.Names}}\t{{.Networks}}"
📌 List All Networks in a Table Format
bash
Copy
Edit
docker network ls --format "table {{.ID}}\t{{.Networks}}"
🎯 You’ve now mastered Docker images, networks, and container management! 🚀

🔹 Next Steps?

Try mapping multiple containers to the same network
Use docker logs to check container logs
Push an image to Docker Hub
Let me know if you want to add real-world scenarios or examples! 🎯
